# RBAC

This module contains scripts for defining and assigning Azure role-based access control (RBAC) permissions using PowerShell.

## Included Scripts

- `define-roles.ps1` – Creates custom roles with specified actions and scope definitions.
- `assign-role.ps1` – Assigns built-in or custom roles to users, groups, or service principals.

## Purpose

These scripts demonstrate control over Azure resource permissions using modular automation, supporting least-privilege access patterns and administrative clarity.

## Notes

- Role definitions follow Azure RBAC schema with customizable `Actions`, `NotActions`, and `AssignableScopes`.
- Assignments rely on valid principal IDs and scoped resource contexts.



